refactor(core): extract L1 trust-layer into packages/kinetik-core

Move identity, heartbeat, proof, proofShare, sensors, and stableJson
out of src/lib/ into a self-contained internal package with its own
package.json, README, and a single public src/index.ts barrel.

App components (VaultPanel, ProofOfOrigin) now import exclusively
through the barrel front door instead of reaching into individual
modules. The barrel is the contract every future external integrator
will depend on.

Also update doc/comment references throughout the repo to point at
the new location. Historical narrative in STATUS.md "Bugs recently
squashed" entries is preserved verbatim (rewriting it would erase
the move's own provenance).

Zero behavioral change:
- tsc --noEmit clean
- landing/verify/smoketest.mjs: ALL CHECKS PASSED
- landing/verify/smoketest-url.mjs: URL ROUND-TRIP PASSES
- Signed APK already shipped (v1.2.0 was built before this refactor)

Purpose: the boundary is the deliverable. This is the package the
eventual public SDK gets published from once L4 (wallet + 1% fee
path) ships and the brand attestor key (rung 8) is anchored. Until
then, private: true and internal-only — the boundary exists for
hygiene, not for distribution.
